{{Infobox person | name = Ville Miettinen | image = | caption = Ville Miettinen in 2007 | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1975|6|5}} | birth_place = [[Geneva]], [[Switzerland]] | residence = [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]] | nationality = [[Finnish people|Finnish]] | known_for = [[Entrepreneurship]] | occupation = [[CEO]], [[Angel investor]] | alma_mater = [[University of Helsinki]] | relatives = [[:fi:Tuomas Vimma|Tuomas Vimma]] (Brother), [[:fi:Jorma K. Miettinen|Jorma K. Miettinen]] (Grandfather) }}
'''Ville Ilmari Miettinen''' (Born June 5, 1975 in [[Geneva]], [[Switzerland]]) is a Finnish [[Entrepreneur#Serial entrepreneur|serial entrepreneur]] and [[computer programmer]]. Miettinen was the co-founder and CTO of [[Hybrid Graphics]], a graphics technology company acquired by [[NVIDIA]] in 2006.<ref name="NVIDIA-acquisition">[[NVIDIA]] press release: [http://www.nvidia.com/object/IO_30518.html ''NVIDIA Corporation to Acquire Hybrid Graphics''], March 22, 2006</ref> Miettinen is a founding partner at Lots,<ref>[http://www.arcticstartup.com/2009/07/24/government-backed-accelerators-chosen-march-on-finland/ Arctic Startup: Government-Backed Accelerators Chosen - March on Finland], July 24, 2009</ref> one of the accelerators in the Finnish governmental Vigo Programme.<ref>[http://www.vigo.fi/frontpage Vigo programme home page]</ref> Miettinen is also the CEO and co-founder of the [[crowdsourcing]] technology company [[Microtask]].<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2010/10/31/business/31digi.html?_r=2&scp=1&sq=microtask&st=cse New York Times: When the Assembly Line Moves Online], October 31, 2010</ref><ref>[http://www.microtask.com/company/management/ Microtask management]</ref>
==Entrepreneurship and venturing== Miettinen is the chairman of the board of the [[ACM SIGGRAPH]] Helsinki Chapter,<ref>[http://chapters.siggraph.org/acm_rss_pc.php ACM SIGGRAPH Chapters]</ref> an advisory board member of [[International Game Developers Association|IGDA]] Finland,<ref>[http://igda.fi/?p=1403 IGDA Finland: New Advisory Board Members], December 27, 2010</ref> a referrer at the European pre-seed venture fund HackFwd,<ref>[http://hackfwd.com/people/ HackFwd people]</ref><ref>[http://www.arcticstartup.com/2010/11/09/hackfwd-has-come-to-finland Arctic Startup:HackFwd has come to Finland], 9 November 2010</ref> and a startup mentor at Aalto Venture Garage.<ref>[http://aaltovg.com/coaches/ Aalto Venture Garage Coaches]</ref> He has held board seats in a number of graphics and gaming related companies, including Fake Graphics,<ref>[http://www.crunchbase.com/company/fake-graphics CrunchBase on Fake Graphics]</ref> [[Xiha Life|Xiha]],<ref>[http://www.technopolisonline.com/index.php?article_id=19493&blogPage_id=193&showPage=true XIHA Closes First Round Financing - Finland Enjoys Increased Activity in VC Investments], 26 January 2010</ref> [[Recoil Games]], Ardites (merged with [[Symbio]] <ref>[http://gigaom.com/2009/09/22/symbio-makes-a-global-play-with-merger/ GigaOm: Symbio Makes a Global Play With Merger], 22 Sep, 2009</ref>), and [[Cowboy Rodeo]]. He is also a technical advisory board member at the fabless semiconductor company Movidius<ref>[http://www.movidius.com/technical-advisory-board/ Movidius Technical Advisory Board]</ref> and a referrer with the European pre-seed investment company [[HackFwd]].<ref>http://hackfwd.com/people/#ville-%22wili%22-miettinen</ref>
==Graphics industry technology focus== Miettinen was actively involved in the [[Khronos Group]], participating in the standardization of [[OpenGL ES]], [[OpenVG]] and [[OpenKODE]], as well as in the [[Java Community Process]] where he contributed to the [[Mobile 3D Graphics API|JSR-184, JSR-297]], and [[Java Bindings for OpenGL|JSR-239]] standards. He is the co-author of the [[DPVS|SurRender]] 3D engine and the [[dPVS]] occlusion culling middleware.<ref>[http://research.nvidia.com/publication/dpvs-occlusion-culling-system-massive-dynamic-environments dPVS: An Occlusion Culling System for Massive Dynamic Environments]</ref>
Miettinen is a frequent lecturer at various universities and industry events, such as [[Game Developers Conference]], [[SIGGRAPH]],<ref>[http://www.siggraph.org/s2005/main.php?f=conference&p=courses&s=35 SIGGRAPH 2005 courses]</ref> [[Eurographics|EUROGRAPHICS]]<ref>[http://www.cg.tuwien.ac.at/events/EG06/program-t1005.php Eurographics 2006: Developing Mobile 3D Applications with OpenGL ES and M3G]</ref> and CrowdConf.<ref>[http://crowdconf.com/possibleimpossible.html CrowdConf 2010: Possible vs. Impossible: Determining the Power of Crowdsourcing]</ref> He also contributes to different blogs related to crowdsourcing<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.microtask.com/blog |title=Microtask Blog |access-date=2011-01-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110119152525/http://www.microtask.com/blog/ |archive-date=2011-01-19 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>[http://dailycrowdsource.com/author/ville-miettinen/ The Daily Crowdsource]</ref> and entrepreneurship.<ref>[http://www.boardman2020.fi/authors/5 Boardman2020 Blog] (in Finnish)</ref>
Miettinen is an avid hobbyist photographer.<ref>[http://designora.com/inspiration/hdr-photography-wilihybrid/ Artist Spotlight: Totally Overdone HDR Photography (& Lovin' It!)] 02 Apr, 2010</ref>
